<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="370" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,258,834]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,699,724]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[603,790,699,723]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordidipennis">
<emphasis box="[603,790,699,723]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="370">M. sordidipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be differentiated from the latter by the characters of male abdomen and genitalia: 
<number box="[511,525,738,762]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370" value="2.0">2</number>
nd abdominal sternal apodemes with posterior lobes robust, length about 
<number box="[1333,1368,737,762]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times basal width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1214,809,834]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,258,834]" box="[199,1214,809,834]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,809,834]" pageId="9" pageNumber="370">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[580,665,810,834]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[580,665,810,834]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="370">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the very slender shaft of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
